Validation: Short Disordered Peptides. To follow up on our dipeptide solution results and further test the applicability of these parameters to larger biomolecules, we turned to simulations of short (3−5 residue) peptides. In particular, we simulated the Gly3, Val3, and Ala5 peptides, which have previously been characterized extensively using NMR spectroscopy by Graf et al.43 and which we utilized in optimizing and validating a change to the ϕ′ backbone dihedral angle potential in ff99SB.11 (In this previous work, we modified just the n = 2 term of the ϕ′ backbone dihedral angle potential in AMBER

