indicating that both ff99SB and ff99SB with the optimized van
der Waals parameters are sufficiently accurate to capture the
conformational ensemble of Gly3 (Table 1). In addition, these data suggest that there are no substantial differences between
the two conformational ensembles and therefore that the
simulated conformational ensembles of very short peptides do not depend strongly on the solvent−solute van der Waals
interactions, at least within the regimes sampled by our work.
